overhaul CET6+

动词读作 ˌəʊvəˈhɔːl 。名词读作 ˈəʊvəˌhɔːl 。 

1. V-T If a piece of equipment is overhauled , it is cleaned, checked thoroughly, and repaired if necessary. 全面检修 [usu passive] 

例： They had ensured the plumbing was overhauled a year ago. 他们确保管道设备一年前已被彻底检修过。 

2. N-COUNT Overhaul is also a noun. 全面检修 

例： ...the overhaul of a cruiser. …一艘巡洋舰的全面检修。 

3. V-T If you overhaul a system or method, you examine it carefully and make many changes in it in order to improve it. 改革; 修订 

例： ...proposals to overhaul bank regulations. …修订银行规章的提议。 

4. N-COUNT Overhaul is also a noun. 改革; 修订 

例： The study says there must be a complete overhaul of air traffic control systems. 研究称必须对航空交通管理系统进行彻底的改革。

